    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-03-18T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-03-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="47"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860F.00/692: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Carr</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-18T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 18, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 18—2:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Your No. 15, March 17. The entire press here is under strict German control,
                    the Gestapo is everywhere and it would be virtual suicide for anyone to publish
                    the statement unless indeed it first appeared in Berlin press.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
